OL,7,FDespite years of Fiona pleading for
OL,8,Fhelp for her son, who had a documented
OL,9,Fhistory of mental health crises and
OL,10,Fabuse in the community, Christopher
OL,11,Fwas never given a mental capacity
OL,12,Fassessment to determine what support
OL,13,Fhe needed.
OL,15,FThat chasm of support left him open to
OL,16,Fexploitation and unable to look after
OL,17,Fhimself in a city hundreds of miles
OL,18,Faway from his family home, while Fiona
OL,19,Ffelt dismissed as "just a fussing
OL,20,Fmother" by those in charge of his care.
