OL,7,FHe initially lived with family members
OL,8,Fwith hopes of studying at university,
OL,9,Fbut due to a lack of support and
OL,10,Funderstanding of his needs from
OL,11,Fauthorities, Christopher struggled and
OL,12,Fmoved out to live independently. But
OL,13,Fhe couldn't fend for himself.
OL,15,FIn the years that followed, he
OL,16,Fattempted suicide, was a victim of
OL,17,Ftheft, had to be rescued by emergency
OL,18,Fservices after accidentally causing a
OL,19,Ffire and was assaulted and exploited
OL,20,Fon numerous occasions.
