OL,7,FFiona visited as often as she could,
OL,8,Fconstantly asked police for welfare
OL,9,Fchecks and urged authorities to help.
OL,11,F"They were getting the letters, they
OL,12,Fwere receiving them, they just weren't
OL,13,Facting on them," she says. "They were
OL,14,Ftelling me, 'You know, you can't wrap
OL,15,Fhim in cotton wool, he's a grown up
OL,16,Fnow' - like I was just a fussing
OL,17,Fmother. It was appalling."
OL,19,FIn November 2016, she received the
OL,20,Fdevastating news she had feared for
OL,21,Fyears ` that Christopher was dead.
