OL,3,CMPs call for change in mental capacity
OL,4,Claw after autistic man killed in own
OL,5,Chome
OL,7,FHowever, research has found that such
OL,8,Fassessments are either not carried out
OL,9,Fenough or are not carried out
OL,10,Feffectively in particular on autistic
OL,11,Fpeople, adults with learning
OL,12,Fdisabilities or mental health issues
OL,13,Fsuch as bipolar, whose insistence they
OL,14,Fcan cope, is often taken at face value
OL,15,Fwithout considering their past history
OL,16,Fand relatives' concerns. This means
OL,17,Fthat - as in Christopher's case - they
OL,18,Fare left without the support they need.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G16/33
